"SendFilesDescription" = "To send a file to your Android device, click on the Share icon or right-click on the file and select \"Share\". Afterward, select \"QuickDrop\" from the list of apps and follow the instructions.

If you don't see QuickDrop in the list, click on \"Edit Extensions\", scroll down, and enable the toggle for QuickDrop.";

"UserManualDescription" = "When QuickDrop is running, it will appear in the menu bar at the top of your screen. Click the QuickDrop icon if you would like to stop receiving files.
            
To send files from your Android device to your Mac, tap on the share icon on your phone, and select \"Quick Share\" or \"Nearby Share\". Your Mac will be listed as an available device.

Important: Your Android device and your Mac need to be on the same WiFi network to transfer files. If you are promted to allow incoming connections, please allow them.";

"TroubleshootingDescription" = "If your Mac does not show up on your Android device or the transmission failed, try the following:

1) Make sure that both devices are connected to the same WiFi network. 2) Restart QuickDrop by clicking the menu bar icon, choose the last entry, and open the app again. 3) Restart your Android device.

If you still encounter issues, the issues could be caused due to your WiFi router. Some routers don't allow devices to communicate with each other. Try to make sure that this setting is set appropriately in your router settings. If you cannot change this setting, enable WiFi Hotspot on your Android device and connect your Mac to your hotspot directly.";


